osfield, Essex, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1337–20 June 1404":"1337–20 juni 1404","1337–1404":"1337–1404","1332–1400":"1332–1400","1360–1434":"1360–1434","1302–1337":"1302–1337","1310–Female":"1310–Overleden","1404":"1404","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1434":"1434","1400":"1400","1354":"1354","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","20 June 1404":"20 juni 1404","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","Gosfield, Essex, England":"Gosfield, Essex, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Toppesfield, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1337–20 June 1404":"1337–20 June 1404","1337–1404":"1337–1404","1332–1400":"1332–1400","1360–1434":"1360–1434","1302–1337":"1302–1337","1310–Female":"1310–Deceased","1404":"1404","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1434":"1434","1400":"1400","1354":"1354","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","20 June 1404":"20 June 1404","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","Gosfield, Essex, England":"Gosfield, Essex, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gates","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of <b>Gate</b> with plural or excrescent <i>-s</i>. The English surname <i>Gate</i> has three possible origins: (i) a topographic name from Middle English <i>gate</i> ‘gate’ (Old English <i>geat</i>, dative plural <i>gatum</i>), denoting someone who lived by a gate or set of gates (possibly sometimes an occupational name for a gate keeper; compre Yates); (ii) in northern England, the East Midlands, and East Anglia, a topographic name from Middle English <i>gate</i> ‘street, road, path’ (Old Norse <i>gata</i>) for someone who lived by a road (compare   Street  ); (iii) a nickname meaning ‘goat’, from northern Middle English <i>gate</i>, <i>gait</i> (Old English <i>gāt</i>, Old Norse <i>geitr</i>).","Americanized form of German <b>Götz</b> (see   Goetz  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French <b>Barrière</b> (see   Barriere  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Street","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>stret(e)</i> ‘street, Roman road’ (Old English <i>strǣt</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived in the main street of a village or town or by a Roman road, or habitational, from a place so named, such as Street (Kent, Herefordshire, Somerset), Street on the Fosse (Somerset), Strete in Blackawton (Devon), Strete Raleigh in Whimple (Devon), or Streat (Sussex). In the Middle Ages the word at first denoted a Roman road but later also came to denote the main street in a town or village.","Americanized form (translation into English) of Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Strasser   and a number of other surnames with similar meaning.","Americanized form of Jewish (from Morocco) <b>Chetrit</b>: perhaps from the Arabic verbal root <i>shṭr</i> ‘to become skillful, dexterous, astute’. The exact origin of the suffix <i>–it</i> is unclear."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Gates was born in 1337, in Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Wesley Gates II, was 35 and her mother, Mrs John Wesley Gates, was 27. She married John Crochrode in 1354, in Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 20 June 1404, in Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1337–20 June 1404":"1337–20. juuni 1404","1337–1404":"1337–1404","1332–1400":"1332–1400","1360–1434":"1360–1434","1302–1337":"1302–1337","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1404":"1404","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1434":"1434","1400":"1400","1354":"1354","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","20 June 1404":"20. juuni 1404","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","Gosfield, Essex, England":"Gosfield, Essex, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Toppesfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1337–20 June 1404":"1337–20. kesäkuuta 1404","1337–1404":"1337–1404","1332–1400":"1332–1400","1360–1434":"1360–1434","1302–1337":"1302–1337","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1404":"1404","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1434":"1434","1400":"1400","1354":"1354","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","20 June 1404":"20. kesäkuuta 1404","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","Gosfield, Essex, England":"Gosfield, Essex, England","Gosfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Gosfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Toppesfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Toppesfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1337–20 June 1404":"1337–20 juin 1404","1337–1404":"1337–1404","1332–1400":"1332–1400